285void ChannelReceive::OnReceivedPayloadData(
286 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> payload,
287 const RTPHeader& rtpHeader) {
288 if (!Playing()) {
289 // Avoid inserting into NetEQ when we are not playing. Count the
290 // packet as discarded.
291
292 // If we have a source_tracker_, tell it that the frame has been
293 // "delivered". Normally, this happens in AudioReceiveStream when audio
294 // frames are pulled out, but when playout is muted, nothing is pulling
295 // frames. The downside of this approach is that frames delivered this way
296 // won't be delayed for playout, and therefore will be unsynchronized with
297 // (a) audio delay when playing and (b) any audio/video synchronization. But
298 // the alternative is that muting playout also stops the SourceTracker from
299 // updating RtpSource information.
300 if (source_tracker_) {
301 RtpPacketInfos::vector_type packet_vector = {
302 RtpPacketInfo(rtpHeader, clock_->CurrentTime())};
303 source_tracker_->OnFrameDelivered(RtpPacketInfos(packet_vector));
304 }
305
306 return;
307 }
308
309 // Push the incoming payload (parsed and ready for decoding) into the ACM
310 if (acm_receiver_.InsertPacket(rtpHeader, payload) != 0) {
311 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR) << "ChannelReceive::OnReceivedPayloadData() unable to "
312 "push data to the ACM";
313 return;
314 }
315
316 int64_t round_trip_time = 0;
317 rtp_rtcp_->RTT(remote_ssrc_, &round_trip_time, NULL, NULL, NULL);
318
319 std::vector<uint16_t> nack_list = acm_receiver_.GetNackList(round_trip_time);
320 if (!nack_list.empty()) {
321 // Can't use nack_list.data() since it's not supported by all
322 // compilers.
323 ResendPackets(&(nack_list[0]), static_cast<int>(nack_list.size()));
324 }
325}
326
327void ChannelReceive::InitFrameTransformerDelegate(
328 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) {
329 RTC_DCHECK(frame_transformer);
330 RTC_DCHECK(!frame_transformer_delegate_);
331
332 // Pass a callback to ChannelReceive::OnReceivedPayloadData, to be called by
333 // the delegate to receive transformed audio.
334 ChannelReceiveFrameTransformerDelegate::ReceiveFrameCallback
335 receive_audio_callback = [this](rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> packet,
336 const RTPHeader& header) {
337 OnReceivedPayloadData(packet, header);
338 };
339 frame_transformer_delegate_ =
340 rtc::make_ref_counted<ChannelReceiveFrameTransformerDelegate>(
341 std::move(receive_audio_callback), std::move(frame_transformer),
342 rtc::Thread::Current());
343 frame_transformer_delegate_->Init();
344}
345
346AudioMixer::Source::AudioFrameInfo ChannelReceive::GetAudioFrameWithInfo(
347 int sample_rate_hz,
348 AudioFrame* audio_frame) {
349 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&audio_thread_race_checker_);
350 audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_ = sample_rate_hz;
351
352 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventAudioPlayout>(remote_ssrc_));
353
354 // Get 10ms raw PCM data from the ACM (mixer limits output frequency)
355 bool muted;
356 if (acm_receiver_.GetAudio(audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_, audio_frame,
357 &muted) == -1) {
358 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR)
359 << "ChannelReceive::GetAudioFrame() PlayoutData10Ms() failed!";
360 // In all likelihood, the audio in this frame is garbage. We return an
361 // error so that the audio mixer module doesn't add it to the mix. As
362 // a result, it won't be played out and the actions skipped here are
363 // irrelevant.
364 return AudioMixer::Source::AudioFrameInfo::kError;
365 }
366
367 if (muted) {
368 // TODO(henrik.lundin): We should be able to do better than this. But we
369 // will have to go through all the cases below where the audio samples may
370 // be used, and handle the muted case in some way.
371 AudioFrameOperations::Mute(audio_frame);
372 }
373
374 {
375 // Pass the audio buffers to an optional sink callback, before applying
376 // scaling/panning, as that applies to the mix operation.
377 // External recipients of the audio (e.g. via AudioTrack), will do their
378 // own mixing/dynamic processing.
379 MutexLock lock(&callback_mutex_);
380 if (audio_sink_) {
381 AudioSinkInterface::Data data(
382 audio_frame->data(), audio_frame->samples_per_channel_,
383 audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_, audio_frame->num_channels_,
384 audio_frame->timestamp_);
385 audio_sink_->OnData(data);
386 }
387 }
388
389 float output_gain = 1.0f;
390 {
391 MutexLock lock(&volume_settings_mutex_);
392 output_gain = _outputGain;
393 }
394
395 // Output volume scaling
396 if (output_gain < 0.99f || output_gain > 1.01f) {
397 // TODO(solenberg): Combine with mute state - this can cause clicks!
398 AudioFrameOperations::ScaleWithSat(output_gain, audio_frame);
399 }
400
401 // Measure audio level (0-9)
402 // TODO(henrik.lundin) Use the |muted| information here too.
403 // TODO(deadbeef): Use RmsLevel for |_outputAudioLevel| (see
404 // https://crbug.com/webrtc/7517).
405 _outputAudioLevel.ComputeLevel(*audio_frame, kAudioSampleDurationSeconds);
406
407 if (capture_start_rtp_time_stamp_ < 0 && audio_frame->timestamp_ != 0) {
408 // The first frame with a valid rtp timestamp.
409 capture_start_rtp_time_stamp_ = audio_frame->timestamp_;
410 }
411
412 if (capture_start_rtp_time_stamp_ >= 0) {
413 // audio_frame.timestamp_ should be valid from now on.
414
415 // Compute elapsed time.
416 int64_t unwrap_timestamp =
417 rtp_ts_wraparound_handler_->Unwrap(audio_frame->timestamp_);
418 audio_frame->elapsed_time_ms_ =
419 (unwrap_timestamp - capture_start_rtp_time_stamp_) /
420 (GetRtpTimestampRateHz() / 1000);
421
422 {
423 MutexLock lock(&ts_stats_lock_);
424 // Compute ntp time.
425 audio_frame->ntp_time_ms_ =
426 ntp_estimator_.Estimate(audio_frame->timestamp_);
427 // |ntp_time_ms_| won't be valid until at least 2 RTCP SRs are received.
428 if (audio_frame->ntp_time_ms_ > 0) {
429 // Compute |capture_start_ntp_time_ms_| so that
430 // |capture_start_ntp_time_ms_| + |elapsed_time_ms_| == |ntp_time_ms_|
431 capture_start_ntp_time_ms_ =
432 audio_frame->ntp_time_ms_ - audio_frame->elapsed_time_ms_;
433 }
434 }
435 }
436
437 {
438 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_1000("WebRTC.Audio.TargetJitterBufferDelayMs",
439 acm_receiver_.TargetDelayMs());
440 const int jitter_buffer_delay = acm_receiver_.FilteredCurrentDelayMs();
441 MutexLock lock(&video_sync_lock_);
442 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_1000("WebRTC.Audio.ReceiverDelayEstimateMs",
443 jitter_buffer_delay + playout_delay_ms_);
444 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_1000("WebRTC.Audio.ReceiverJitterBufferDelayMs",
445 jitter_buffer_delay);
446 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_1000("WebRTC.Audio.ReceiverDeviceDelayMs",
447 playout_delay_ms_);
448 }
449
450 return muted ? AudioMixer::Source::AudioFrameInfo::kMuted
451 : AudioMixer::Source::AudioFrameInfo::kNormal;
452}

454int ChannelReceive::PreferredSampleRate() const {
455 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&audio_thread_race_checker_);
456 // Return the bigger of playout and receive frequency in the ACM.
457 return std::max(acm_receiver_.last_packet_sample_rate_hz().value_or(0),
458 acm_receiver_.last_output_sample_rate_hz());
459}

465ChannelReceive::ChannelReceive(
466 Clock* clock,
467 ProcessThread* module_process_thread,
468 NetEqFactory* neteq_factory,
469 AudioDeviceModule* audio_device_module,
470 Transport* rtcp_send_transport,
471 RtcEventLog* rtc_event_log,
472 uint32_t local_ssrc,
473 uint32_t remote_ssrc,
474 size_t jitter_buffer_max_packets,
475 bool jitter_buffer_fast_playout,
476 int jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms,
477 bool jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling,
478 rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioDecoderFactory> decoder_factory,
479 absl::optional<AudioCodecPairId> codec_pair_id,
480 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor,
481 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
482 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer)
483 : event_log_(rtc_event_log),
484 rtp_receive_statistics_(ReceiveStatistics::Create(clock)),
485 remote_ssrc_(remote_ssrc),
486 acm_receiver_(AcmConfig(neteq_factory,
487 decoder_factory,
488 codec_pair_id,
489 jitter_buffer_max_packets,
490 jitter_buffer_fast_playout)),
491 _outputAudioLevel(),
492 clock_(clock),
493 ntp_estimator_(clock),
494 playout_timestamp_rtp_(0),
495 playout_delay_ms_(0),
496 rtp_ts_wraparound_handler_(new rtc::TimestampWrapAroundHandler()),
497 capture_start_rtp_time_stamp_(-1),
498 capture_start_ntp_time_ms_(-1),
499 module_process_thread_(module_process_thread),
500 _audioDeviceModulePtr(audio_device_module),
501 _outputGain(1.0f),
502 associated_send_channel_(nullptr),
503 frame_decryptor_(frame_decryptor),
504 crypto_options_(crypto_options),
505 absolute_capture_time_receiver_(clock) {
506 RTC_DCHECK(module_process_thread_);
507 RTC_DCHECK(audio_device_module);
508
509 acm_receiver_.ResetInitialDelay();
510 acm_receiver_.SetMinimumDelay(0);
511 acm_receiver_.SetMaximumDelay(0);
512 acm_receiver_.FlushBuffers();
513
514 _outputAudioLevel.ResetLevelFullRange();
515
516 rtp_receive_statistics_->EnableRetransmitDetection(remote_ssrc_, true);
517 RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration configuration;
518 configuration.clock = clock;
519 configuration.audio = true;
520 configuration.receiver_only = true;
521 configuration.outgoing_transport = rtcp_send_transport;
522 configuration.receive_statistics = rtp_receive_statistics_.get();
523 configuration.event_log = event_log_;
524 configuration.local_media_ssrc = local_ssrc;
525
526 if (frame_transformer)
527 InitFrameTransformerDelegate(std::move(frame_transformer));
528
529 rtp_rtcp_ = ModuleRtpRtcpImpl2::Create(configuration);
530 rtp_rtcp_->SetSendingMediaStatus(false);
531 rtp_rtcp_->SetRemoteSSRC(remote_ssrc_);
532
533 // Ensure that RTCP is enabled for the created channel.
534 rtp_rtcp_->SetRTCPStatus(RtcpMode::kCompound);
535
536 // TODO(tommi): This should be an implementation detail of ModuleRtpRtcpImpl2
537 // and the pointer to the process thread should be there (which also localizes
538 // the problem of getting rid of that dependency).
539 module_process_thread_->RegisterModule(rtp_rtcp_.get(), RTC_FROM_HERE);
540}
541
542ChannelReceive::~ChannelReceive() {
543 RTC_DCHECK(construction_thread_.IsCurrent());
544
545 // Unregister the module before stopping playout etc, to match the order
546 // things were set up in the ctor.
547 module_process_thread_->DeRegisterModule(rtp_rtcp_.get());
548
549 // Resets the delegate's callback to ChannelReceive::OnReceivedPayloadData.
550 if (frame_transformer_delegate_)
551 frame_transformer_delegate_->Reset();
552
553 StopPlayout();
554}

556void ChannelReceive::SetSink(AudioSinkInterface* sink) {
557 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
558 MutexLock lock(&callback_mutex_);
559 audio_sink_ = sink;
560}

562void ChannelReceive::StartPlayout() {
563 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
564 MutexLock lock(&playing_lock_);
565 playing_ = true;
566}
567
568void ChannelReceive::StopPlayout() {
569 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
570 MutexLock lock(&playing_lock_);
571 playing_ = false;
572 _outputAudioLevel.ResetLevelFullRange();
573}

575absl::optional<std::pair<int, SdpAudioFormat>> ChannelReceive::GetReceiveCodec()
576 const {
577 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
578 return acm_receiver_.LastDecoder();
579}
580
581void ChannelReceive::SetReceiveCodecs(
582 const std::map<int, SdpAudioFormat>& codecs) {
583 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
584 for (const auto& kv : codecs) {
585 RTC_DCHECK_GE(kv.second.clockrate_hz, 1000);
586 payload_type_frequencies_[kv.first] = kv.second.clockrate_hz;
587 }
588 acm_receiver_.SetCodecs(codecs);
589}
590
591void ChannelReceive::OnRtpPacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
592 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
593 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Expect to be called exclusively on the
594 // network thread. Once that's done, the same applies to
595 // UpdatePlayoutTimestamp and
596 int64_t now_ms = rtc::TimeMillis();
597
598 {
599 MutexLock lock(&sync_info_lock_);
600 last_received_rtp_timestamp_ = packet.Timestamp();
601 last_received_rtp_system_time_ms_ = now_ms;
602 }
603
604 // Store playout timestamp for the received RTP packet
605 UpdatePlayoutTimestamp(false, now_ms);
606
607 const auto& it = payload_type_frequencies_.find(packet.PayloadType());
608 if (it == payload_type_frequencies_.end())
609 return;
610 // TODO(nisse): Set payload_type_frequency earlier, when packet is parsed.
611 RtpPacketReceived packet_copy(packet);
612 packet_copy.set_payload_type_frequency(it->second);
613
614 rtp_receive_statistics_->OnRtpPacket(packet_copy);
615
616 RTPHeader header;
617 packet_copy.GetHeader(&header);
618
619 // Interpolates absolute capture timestamp RTP header extension.
620 header.extension.absolute_capture_time =
621 absolute_capture_time_receiver_.OnReceivePacket(
622 AbsoluteCaptureTimeReceiver::GetSource(header.ssrc,
623 header.arrOfCSRCs),
624 header.timestamp,
625 rtc::saturated_cast<uint32_t>(packet_copy.payload_type_frequency()),
626 header.extension.absolute_capture_time);
627
628 ReceivePacket(packet_copy.data(), packet_copy.size(), header);
629}
630
631void ChannelReceive::ReceivePacket(const uint8_t* packet,
632 size_t packet_length,
633 const RTPHeader& header) {
634 const uint8_t* payload = packet + header.headerLength;
635 assert(packet_length >= header.headerLength);
636 size_t payload_length = packet_length - header.headerLength;
637
638 size_t payload_data_length = payload_length - header.paddingLength;
639
640 // E2EE Custom Audio Frame Decryption (This is optional).
641 // Keep this buffer around for the lifetime of the OnReceivedPayloadData call.
642 rtc::Buffer decrypted_audio_payload;
643 if (frame_decryptor_ != nullptr) {
644 const size_t max_plaintext_size = frame_decryptor_->GetMaxPlaintextByteSize(
645 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, payload_length);
646 decrypted_audio_payload.SetSize(max_plaintext_size);
647
648 const std::vector<uint32_t> csrcs(header.arrOfCSRCs,
649 header.arrOfCSRCs + header.numCSRCs);
650 const FrameDecryptorInterface::Result decrypt_result =
651 frame_decryptor_->Decrypt(
652 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, csrcs,
653 /*additional_data=*/nullptr,
654 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t>(payload, payload_data_length),
655 decrypted_audio_payload);
656
657 if (decrypt_result.IsOk()) {
658 decrypted_audio_payload.SetSize(decrypt_result.bytes_written);
659 } else {
660 // Interpret failures as a silent frame.
661 decrypted_audio_payload.SetSize(0);
662 }
663
664 payload = decrypted_audio_payload.data();
665 payload_data_length = decrypted_audio_payload.size();
666 } else if (crypto_options_.sframe.require_frame_encryption) {
667 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR)
668 << "FrameDecryptor required but not set, dropping packet";
669 payload_data_length = 0;
670 }
671
672 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> payload_data(payload, payload_data_length);
673 if (frame_transformer_delegate_) {
674 // Asynchronously transform the received payload. After the payload is
675 // transformed, the delegate will call OnReceivedPayloadData to handle it.
676 frame_transformer_delegate_->Transform(payload_data, header, remote_ssrc_);
677 } else {
678 OnReceivedPayloadData(payload_data, header);
679 }
680}
681
682void ChannelReceive::ReceivedRTCPPacket(const uint8_t* data, size_t length) {
683 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
684 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Expect to be called exclusively on the
685 // network thread.
686
687 // Store playout timestamp for the received RTCP packet
688 UpdatePlayoutTimestamp(true, rtc::TimeMillis());
689
690 // Deliver RTCP packet to RTP/RTCP module for parsing
691 rtp_rtcp_->IncomingRtcpPacket(data, length);
692
693 int64_t rtt = GetRTT();
694 if (rtt == 0) {
695 // Waiting for valid RTT.
696 return;
697 }
698
699 uint32_t ntp_secs = 0;
700 uint32_t ntp_frac = 0;
701 uint32_t rtp_timestamp = 0;
702 if (rtp_rtcp_->RemoteNTP(&ntp_secs, &ntp_frac,
703 /*rtcp_arrival_time_secs=*/nullptr,
704 /*rtcp_arrival_time_frac=*/nullptr,
705 &rtp_timestamp) != 0) {
706 // Waiting for RTCP.
707 return;
708 }
709
710 {
711 MutexLock lock(&ts_stats_lock_);
712 ntp_estimator_.UpdateRtcpTimestamp(rtt, ntp_secs, ntp_frac, rtp_timestamp);
713 absl::optional<int64_t> remote_to_local_clock_offset_ms =
714 ntp_estimator_.EstimateRemoteToLocalClockOffsetMs();
715 if (remote_to_local_clock_offset_ms.has_value()) {
716 absolute_capture_time_receiver_.SetRemoteToLocalClockOffset(
717 Int64MsToQ32x32(*remote_to_local_clock_offset_ms));
718 }
719 }
720}

760CallReceiveStatistics ChannelReceive::GetRTCPStatistics() const {
761 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
762 CallReceiveStatistics stats;
763
764 // The jitter statistics is updated for each received RTP packet and is based
765 // on received packets.
766 RtpReceiveStats rtp_stats;
767 StreamStatistician* statistician =
768 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(remote_ssrc_);
769 if (statistician) {
770 rtp_stats = statistician->GetStats();
771 }
772
773 stats.cumulativeLost = rtp_stats.packets_lost;
774 stats.jitterSamples = rtp_stats.jitter;
775
776 stats.rttMs = GetRTT();
777
778 // Data counters.
779 if (statistician) {
780 stats.payload_bytes_rcvd = rtp_stats.packet_counter.payload_bytes;
781
782 stats.header_and_padding_bytes_rcvd =
783 rtp_stats.packet_counter.header_bytes +
784 rtp_stats.packet_counter.padding_bytes;
785 stats.packetsReceived = rtp_stats.packet_counter.packets;
786 stats.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms =
787 rtp_stats.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms;
788 } else {
789 stats.payload_bytes_rcvd = 0;
790 stats.header_and_padding_bytes_rcvd = 0;
791 stats.packetsReceived = 0;
792 stats.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms = absl::nullopt;
793 }
794
795 // Timestamps.
796 {
797 MutexLock lock(&ts_stats_lock_);
798 stats.capture_start_ntp_time_ms_ = capture_start_ntp_time_ms_;
799 }
800
801 absl::optional<RtpRtcpInterface::SenderReportStats> rtcp_sr_stats =
802 rtp_rtcp_->GetSenderReportStats();
803 if (rtcp_sr_stats.has_value()) {
804 // Number of seconds since 1900 January 1 00:00 GMT (see
805 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc868).
806 constexpr int64_t kNtpJan1970Millisecs =
807 2208988800 * rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec;
808 stats.last_sender_report_timestamp_ms =
809 rtcp_sr_stats->last_arrival_timestamp.ToMs() - kNtpJan1970Millisecs;
810 stats.last_sender_report_remote_timestamp_ms =
811 rtcp_sr_stats->last_remote_timestamp.ToMs() - kNtpJan1970Millisecs;
812 stats.sender_reports_packets_sent = rtcp_sr_stats->packets_sent;
813 stats.sender_reports_bytes_sent = rtcp_sr_stats->bytes_sent;
814 stats.sender_reports_reports_count = rtcp_sr_stats->reports_count;
815 }
816
817 return stats;
818}

871uint32_t ChannelReceive::GetDelayEstimate() const {
872 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
873

875 {
876 MutexLock lock(&video_sync_lock_);

883bool ChannelReceive::SetMinimumPlayoutDelay(int delay_ms) {
884 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): This should run on the network thread.
885 // We get here via RtpStreamsSynchronizer. Once that's done, many (all?) of
886 // these locks aren't needed.
887 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
888 // Limit to range accepted by both VoE and ACM, so we're at least getting as
889 // close as possible, instead of failing.
890 delay_ms = rtc::SafeClamp(delay_ms, kVoiceEngineMinMinPlayoutDelayMs,
891 kVoiceEngineMaxMinPlayoutDelayMs);
892 if (acm_receiver_.SetMinimumDelay(delay_ms) != 0) {
893 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR)
894 << "SetMinimumPlayoutDelay() failed to set min playout delay";
895 return false;
896 }
897 return true;
898}

904 MutexLock lock(&video_sync_lock_);

906 return false;
907 *rtp_timestamp = playout_timestamp_rtp_;
908 *time_ms = playout_timestamp_rtp_time_ms_.value();
909 return true;
910 }

921absl::optional<int64_t>
922ChannelReceive::GetCurrentEstimatedPlayoutNtpTimestampMs(int64_t now_ms) const {
923 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
924 MutexLock lock(&video_sync_lock_);
925 if (!playout_timestamp_ntp_ || !playout_timestamp_ntp_time_ms_)
926 return absl::nullopt;

940absl::optional<Syncable::Info> ChannelReceive::GetSyncInfo() const {
941 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): This should run on the network thread.
942 // We get here via RtpStreamsSynchronizer. Once that's done, many of
943 // these locks aren't needed.
944 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
945 Syncable::Info info;
946 if (rtp_rtcp_->RemoteNTP(&info.capture_time_ntp_secs,
947 &info.capture_time_ntp_frac,
948 /*rtcp_arrival_time_secs=*/nullptr,
949 /*rtcp_arrival_time_frac=*/nullptr,
950 &info.capture_time_source_clock) != 0) {
951 return absl::nullopt;
952 }
953
954 {
955 MutexLock lock(&sync_info_lock_);
956 if (!last_received_rtp_timestamp_ || !last_received_rtp_system_time_ms_) {
957 return absl::nullopt;
958 }
959 info.latest_received_capture_timestamp = *last_received_rtp_timestamp_;
960 info.latest_receive_time_ms = *last_received_rtp_system_time_ms_;
961 }
962
963 int jitter_buffer_delay = acm_receiver_.FilteredCurrentDelayMs();
964 {
965 MutexLock lock(&video_sync_lock_);
966 info.current_delay_ms = jitter_buffer_delay + playout_delay_ms_;
967 }
968
969 return info;
970}
971
972void ChannelReceive::UpdatePlayoutTimestamp(bool rtcp, int64_t now_ms) {
973 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Expect to be called exclusively on the
974 // network thread. Once that's done, we won't need video_sync_lock_.
975
976 jitter_buffer_playout_timestamp_ = acm_receiver_.GetPlayoutTimestamp();
977
978 if (!jitter_buffer_playout_timestamp_) {
979 // This can happen if this channel has not received any RTP packets. In
980 // this case, NetEq is not capable of computing a playout timestamp.
981 return;
982 }
983
984 uint16_t delay_ms = 0;
985 if (_audioDeviceModulePtr->PlayoutDelay(&delay_ms) == -1) {
986 RTC_DLOG(LS_WARNING)
987 << "ChannelReceive::UpdatePlayoutTimestamp() failed to read"
988 " playout delay from the ADM";
989 return;
990 }
991
992 RTC_DCHECK(jitter_buffer_playout_timestamp_);
993 uint32_t playout_timestamp = *jitter_buffer_playout_timestamp_;
994
995 // Remove the playout delay.
996 playout_timestamp -= (delay_ms * (GetRtpTimestampRateHz() / 1000));
997
998 {
999 MutexLock lock(&video_sync_lock_);
1000 if (!rtcp && playout_timestamp != playout_timestamp_rtp_) {
1001 playout_timestamp_rtp_ = playout_timestamp;
1002 playout_timestamp_rtp_time_ms_ = now_ms;
1003 }
1004 playout_delay_ms_ = delay_ms;
1005 }
1006}
1007
1008int ChannelReceive::GetRtpTimestampRateHz() const {
1009 const auto decoder = acm_receiver_.LastDecoder();
1010 // Default to the playout frequency if we've not gotten any packets yet.
1011 // TODO(ossu): Zero clockrate can only happen if we've added an external
1012 // decoder for a format we don't support internally. Remove once that way of
1013 // adding decoders is gone!
1014 // TODO(kwiberg): `decoder->second.clockrate_hz` is an RTP clockrate as it
1015 // should, but `acm_receiver_.last_output_sample_rate_hz()` is a codec sample
1016 // rate, which is not always the same thing.
1017 return (decoder && decoder->second.clockrate_hz != 0)
1018 ? decoder->second.clockrate_hz
1019 : acm_receiver_.last_output_sample_rate_hz();
1020}
1021
1022int64_t ChannelReceive::GetRTT() const {
1023 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
1024 std::vector<ReportBlockData> report_blocks =
1025 rtp_rtcp_->GetLatestReportBlockData();
1026
1027 if (report_blocks.empty()) {
1028 // Try fall back on an RTT from an associated channel.
1029 if (!associated_send_channel_) {
1030 return 0;
1031 }
1032 return associated_send_channel_->GetRTT();
1033 }
1034
1035 // TODO(nisse): This method computes RTT based on sender reports, even though
1036 // a receive stream is not supposed to do that.
1037 for (const ReportBlockData& data : report_blocks) {
1038 if (data.report_block().sender_ssrc == remote_ssrc_) {
1039 return data.last_rtt_ms();
1040 }
1041 }
1042 return 0;
1043}

1047std::unique_ptr<ChannelReceiveInterface> CreateChannelReceive(
1048 Clock* clock,
1049 ProcessThread* module_process_thread,
1050 NetEqFactory* neteq_factory,
1051 AudioDeviceModule* audio_device_module,
1052 Transport* rtcp_send_transport,
1053 RtcEventLog* rtc_event_log,
1054 uint32_t local_ssrc,
1055 uint32_t remote_ssrc,
1056 size_t jitter_buffer_max_packets,
1057 bool jitter_buffer_fast_playout,
1058 int jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms,
1059 bool jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling,
1060 rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioDecoderFactory> decoder_factory,
1061 absl::optional<AudioCodecPairId> codec_pair_id,
1062 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor,
1063 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
1064 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) {
1065 return std::make_unique<ChannelReceive>(
1066 clock, module_process_thread, neteq_factory, audio_device_module,
1067 rtcp_send_transport, rtc_event_log, local_ssrc, remote_ssrc,
1068 jitter_buffer_max_packets, jitter_buffer_fast_playout,
1069 jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms, jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling,
1070 decoder_factory, codec_pair_id, frame_decryptor, crypto_options,
1071 std::move(frame_transformer));
1072}
